ZH: 这个城市发生了严重的暴动。
EN: A serious riot broke out in the city.

ZH: 暴动导致了很多人受伤。
EN: The riot resulted in many people being injured.

ZH: 社会动荡往往导致暴动的发生。
EN: Social unrest often leads to riots.

ZH: 他们正在试图平息暴动。
EN: They are trying to quell the riot.

ZH: 暴动持续了整整一天。
EN: The riot lasted for a whole day.

ZH: 暴动分子被警方逮捕。
EN: Rioters were arrested by the police.

ZH: 这场暴动给城市带来了严重的损失。
EN: The riot caused serious damage to the city.

ZH: 暴动是无序社会的产物。
EN: Riots are a product of a disordered society.

ZH: 暴动已经蔓延到了全国各地。
EN: The riot has spread to all parts of the country.

ZH: 只有通过对话才能避免暴动发生。
EN: Only through dialogue can riots be prevented.

ZH: 暴动的根源在于人们的不满情绪。
EN: The root cause of riots lies in people's discontent.

ZH: 这次暴动的后果是不可估量的。
EN: The consequences of this riot are immeasurable.

ZH: 对于暴动，政府必须采取果断行动。
EN: The government must take decisive action against riots.

ZH: 暴动给社会治安造成了极大的威胁。
EN: Riots pose a great threat to public security.

ZH: 这场暴动已经引起了国际社会的关注。
EN: This riot has attracted international attention.

ZH: 可以通过改善经济状况来减少暴动的发生。
EN: Improving economic conditions can reduce the occurrence of riots.

ZH: 暴动的发动者往往是受到排斥的少数群体。
EN: The instigators of riots are often marginalized minority groups.

ZH: 手段不对的抗议很容易演变为暴动。
EN: Protests conducted inappropriately can easily escalate into riots.

ZH: 暴动使得市民生活陷入了混乱之中。
EN: The riot plunged the lives of citizens into chaos.
